review_blob: Im sorry. Salt Spring is such a pretty place, but this is a poor example of a Pale Ale.
(500ml bottle) Lovely head, good flavour (lots of spice). Weak, dry, slightly sour finish.

LOL Andrew. Good one!  I think you folks are all missing the point!!! Last year they came out with a 10(10%) to celebrate their 10th anniversary. This year it's 11%. These guys at Unibroue KICK!!! Where can you get that much punch in one bottle this side of the Atlantic (ie. an ocean away from the true land of beers, Belguim)?
I tried this beer on two separate occasions, and it is overated for a wheat beer. There are lots of better ones available.
For a tinned, Canadian, low-cost, swill-style, beer, its the best.

From the 6-pack I tested, 3 bottles were flat (does this speak of quality control?). good hop aroma, weaker in malt than I had hoped.  An unpleasant flavor of cigar butts. Sorry Nelson, your Paddywack is much better.
For a bottled IPA, very good. Well hopped. Nelsons best offering.
Im half way through the bottle. Typical enjoyment from a UNIBROU. Be sure to use the right shaped glass! Lovely white head on a darker than normal wheat beer. Do I taste allspice? perhaps.
